One popular JavaScript library for adding resizable (and often draggable) behavior to UI components is ResizeObserver. ResizeObserver is an API provided by the browser that monitors the size of a DOM element and triggers events when it changes. Here's a basic example of how to use ResizeObserver to create a resizable grid:

```javascript
// Create a ResizeObserver instance
const resizeObserver = new ResizeObserver((entries) => {
  entries.forEach(entry => {
    // Find the resizable element
    const el = entry.target;

    // Resize the element
    el.style.height = el.offsetHeight + 'px';
  });
});

// Add the ResizeObserver to the document
resizeObserver.observe(document.body);
```

This example creates a ResizeObserver instance, which monitors the size of the body element. When the body element changes in size, the ResizeObserver observes that and resizes the grid elements accordingly.

